## Technical Architecture

### Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14.2.35+ (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: CSS Modules (`*.module.css`)
- **Images**: Next.js `next/image` for optimization
- **Animation**: CSS animations + Intersection Observer API

### Project Structure
```
/app
  /components
    ScrollAnimations.tsx    # Scroll-triggered animations
  page.tsx                  # Main page component
  page.module.css           # Page styles
  globals.css               # Global styles & CSS variables
  layout.tsx                # Root layout with metadata
/public
  /images
    logo.webp              # Main logo (100x100px in nav)
    lynne.png              # Instructor photo
    testimonials-zoom.jpg  # Student testimonials grid
    energeticconnectiontosun.jpg  # Survival mode section
    qigongatlabryinth-1080x623.webp  # Tension/pain section
```

### Key Components

#### ScrollAnimations Component
- Client component (`'use client'`)
- Uses Intersection Observer for scroll-triggered animations
- Adds `animate-in` class when elements enter viewport
- Observes sections, cards, and testimonials
- Initializes after DOM ready (50ms timeout)

