## Code Conventions

### CSS Modules
- All component styles in `*.module.css` files
- Class names: camelCase (e.g., `heroTitle`, `ctaPrimary`)
- Use CSS variables from `globals.css` for colors

### TypeScript
- Type-safe props and components
- Use Next.js types (e.g., `Image` component props)

### Component Patterns
- Server components by default (React Server Components)
- Client components only when needed (`'use client'` directive)
- Keep animations in dedicated client component (`ScrollAnimations`)

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (`ScrollAnimations.tsx`)
- CSS classes: camelCase (`heroTitle`)
- Files: lowercase with hyphens or camelCase matching component

